ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime

ElementDescription: Total number of incoming calls
Total number of outgoing calls
Total number of missed calls
Total number of unique incoming callers
Total number of unique outgoing calls
Total number of unique callers missed
Total amount of minutes spent on incoming calls
Total amount of minutes spent on outgoing calls
Total number of unique individuals who called or texted the Beiwe user, or who the Beiwe user called or texted. The total number of individuals with any communication contact with the Beiwe user
Total number of sent SMS texts
Total number of received SMS texts
Total number of sent MMS texts
Total number of received MMS texts
Total number of people who received texts from subject
Total number of people who sent texts to subject
Total number of characters sent
Total number of characters received
The total number of times a text is sent to a unique person without response
The total number of times a text is received by a unique person without response
